[2026-04-26] Session summary — context for this and future smoke runs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Files present (all untracked on branch ongoing-infra):
  - infra/smoke-test.sh                  — I05 driver script, ~159 lines
  - assets/samplesheet-smoke-child.csv   — 2 SRA samples: SRR6664374, SRR6664342
                                           (study_accession=STUDY_SRA)

Known discrepancies vs. the I05 spec (issues/I05-smoke-test.md), still unresolved:
  1. Spec checks MetaPhlAn TSV (*_profile.tsv) for >50 features.
     Script checks the .biom file (*_metaphlan.biom) for >1KB only.
  2. Script hardcodes HUMAnN filename suffixes (_2_genefamilies.tsv,
     _4_pathabundance.tsv) — must match actual workflow output naming.
  These may produce false FAILs at the validation step even with a healthy run.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
First run attempt (DEAD — abandoned mid-pipeline)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project:   smoke-20260426-025416
Launched:  2026-04-26 02:54 UTC, directly via `nextflow run` (NOT through
           smoke-test.sh, so no validation step queued).
Command:   nextflow run main.nf -profile aws \
             --input s3://gutz-nf-reads-profilers-runs/samplesheets/samplesheet-smoke-child.csv \
             --project "smoke-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)" 2>&1 | head -80

Failure mode: stdout piped to `head -80`. Once Nextflow logged past line 80,
`head` closed the pipe; next write SIGPIPE'd the JVM. Driver died silently.

Batch jobs that did run before the driver died (both SUCCEEDED):
  - count_reads_SRR6664342  job 9457be81-34fe-47f9-8518-003a6d593648
  - count_reads_SRR6664374  job a903f000-6737-4a73-8eeb-eee0d45090a2
No clean_reads / profile_taxa / profile_function jobs were ever submitted
because the driver was gone.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lesson for future runs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Never pipe `nextflow run` through `head` / `tail` / any consumer that may close
its stdin early. Redirect to a file with `> log 2>&1`, and use nohup +
background + </dev/null so the driver survives shell exits.

