================================================================================
[2026-04-26] Run #2 result — FAILED (and what we learned)
================================================================================

Outcome: smoke-test.sh exited non-zero. Pipeline progressed to clean_reads (✔ 2/2),
profile_taxa was Submitted, then both profile_function (SRR6664342, SRR6664374)
failed at AWS Batch *job submission* with:

  The user value contains invalid characters.
  Enter a value that matches the pattern ^([a-z0-9_][a-z0-9_-]{0,30})$

Diagnosis: this is what I00 was supposed to fix, but the I00 fix is WRONG.

I00 (commit bb92a21, "Fix containerOptions escaping for AWS Batch") was already
merged into ongoing-infra. It changed:
  containerOptions '-u $(id -u):$(id -g)'   →
  containerOptions '-u \$(id -u):\$(id -g)'
on profile_function (line 67) and combine_humann_tables (line 117).

Why that doesn't fix Batch: in a Groovy single-quoted string, '\$' is the two
literal characters \ and $ — Nextflow forwards them verbatim. On the awsbatch
executor there is no shell to expand $(id -u); Nextflow translates `-u <value>`
into the ECS containerOverride `user` field, which Batch validates against the
regex above. Either form ($(id... or \$(id...) fails identically.

The escape is only meaningful for the local Docker executor, where the host
shell expands $(id -u) before docker run sees it.

Affected processes (all 5 in modules/community_characterisation.nf):
   67  profile_function          — on the live AWS path, will fail every run
  117  combine_humann_tables     — on the live AWS path, will fail next
  235  convert_tables_to_biom    — currently dead code (biom branch commented out in main.nf)
  272  split_stratified_tables   — on the live AWS path, would fail after combine
  305  regroup_genefamilies      — currently dead code

I00 doc claims 235/272/305 "already work correctly on AWS Batch". That claim is
incorrect — those processes either never run (dead code) or haven't been
reached yet (run aborts upstream).

Fix plan (Option B): move containerOptions out of the module and into the local
profile only. conf/test.config gets withName overrides for the 5 processes;
modules/community_characterisation.nf has the lines removed. Net effect:
  - AWS Batch: no `-u` user override, container runs as ECS-default user, Batch
    accepts the job.
  - Local Docker (test profile): same -u $(id -u):$(id -g) as today, output
    files owned by the host user.

