  i-01286181274e20cbc  orphan worker from run #2; job ca68ee62 terminated;
                       Batch will reap the instance shortly
  i-0691d68cb529d0fc4  run-5 worker, OnDemand, will be drained at CE cycle
  i-0cf5db89e17e600bf  run-5 worker, Spot,     will be drained at CE cycle

Run-5 driver: EXITED. Batch queue: empty.

================================================================================
[2026-04-26 ~14:00 UTC] Root cause identified + fix deployed (new session)
================================================================================

Root cause
----------
All 5 runs failed at profile_function (HUMAnN4) because /mnt/dbs/chocophlan_v4_alpha/
did not exist on the worker when the job started. The ECS agent on the AL2023
ECS-optimized AMI auto-starts on boot and registers with Batch BEFORE the
UserData cloud-init script runs. The S3 sync (~65 GiB, 30k objects) hadn't
completed — or even started — by the time Batch scheduled HUMAnN jobs.

MetaPhlAn worked because its DB (9 files, 19.2 GiB) synced faster than
ChocoPhlAn (30,094 files, 41.7 GiB). The per-file overhead of syncing 30k
small files means ChocoPhlAn always finishes last.

Evidence from CloudWatch logs (/aws/batch/job):
  nf-barbarahelena-humann-4-0-3/default/6092d433... → exit 1, 6s
    "CRITICAL ERROR: The directory provided for the ChocoPhlAn database at
     /mnt/dbs/chocophlan_v4_alpha/ does not exist."
  nf-barbarahelena-humann-4-0-3/default/97c7493b... → identical

DB sizes in s3://cjb-gutz-s3-demo/ (excluding referencedata/):
  metaphlan_databases/                    9 files    19.2 GiB
  chocophlan_v4_alpha/                30,094 files   41.7 GiB
  uniref90_annotated_v4_alpha.../         1 file      1.6 GiB
  full_mapping_v4_alpha/                 20 files     2.7 GiB
  Total:                            ~30,124 files   ~65.2 GiB

Fix applied
-----------
infra/batch-stack.yaml UserData now:
  1. Stops ECS agent immediately: systemctl stop ecs
  2. Installs miniconda + awscli
  3. Syncs S3 databases to /mnt/dbs/
  4. Starts ECS agent: systemctl start ecs

Commit: e6aea80 "Fix ECS/S3-sync race condition and add Claude Code agents and skills"

Deployment
----------
  1. CFN stack deployed:
       aws cloudformation deploy --stack-name nf-reads-profiler-batch ...
     Result: Successfully created/updated stack
     Launch template bumped to v10 — confirmed UserData has:
       line 16: systemctl stop ecs
       line 35: /opt/conda-aws/bin/aws s3 sync s3://cjb-gutz-s3-demo /mnt/dbs/ ...
       line 39: systemctl start ecs

  2. CE state-cycle (DISABLED → ENABLED) to force Batch to re-mint its
     merged launch template wrapper from customer LT v10:
       SpotComputeEnvironment-Eyi8eJp5FEi4DwVk    ENABLED / VALID
       OnDemandComputeEnvironme-BlIl26JdB3ef8RMS   ENABLED / VALID

  3. Guardrails hook added (.claude/hooks/guardrails.sh) — nextflow run
     -profile aws now prompts for user confirmation before launching.
     Commit: e552d43

Infrastructure state:
  Stack:           nf-reads-profiler-batch — up to date
  Launch template: v10, stop-ecs guard confirmed
  Both CEs:        ENABLED / VALID
  Job queue:       spot-queue, ENABLED
  Active workers:  0 (will scale up on next run)

Ready for run #6 (first run with the fix).
